dismissalText.commentary: Kamran Akmal c McLaren b Peterson 48 (51b 6x4 1x6 90m) SR: 94.11

dismissalComment.html: caught at backward square leg! Brilliantly done by McLaren! Akmal goes for a sweep and gets a healthy top-edge towards backward square leg. McLaren back-pedals quite some distance and takes this arching backwards

dismissalText.commentary: Younis Khan c Amla b Behardien 29 (58b 2x4 0x6 73m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: oh what a catch! caught at midwicket. It was a long-hop on off stump and Younis swivels on his heels and murders it towards midwicket, but the only thing he doesn't get his elevation and Amla times his jump to pluck it out of nowhere, excellent catch

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c Ingram b Steyn 5 (9b 1x4 0x6 12m) SR: 55.55

dismissalComment.html: caught at second slip! First strike! A Steyn special, it was on a length, angling into the batsman and around off stump, the batsman had to play at that one, but the ball straightened just a bit to square up the batsman and the edge goes flying to the right of the second-slip fielder. South Africa overtake Pakistan at the first corner.. But this is just the first lap...

dismissalText.commentary: Wahab Riaz run out (McLaren/Peterson) 12 (28b 0x4 0x6 50m) SR: 42.85

dismissalComment.html: the batsman dabs the flatter delivery to square leg, but Wahab runs halfway down the pitch. It didn't look like a run at all, the throw comes in from the fielder, and the batsman is nowhere near. Robbie P actually breaks the stumps with his leg, but he realises that in time, so uproots the stump to complete the run out. Wahab was still nowhere near.

commentTextItems.html: moves outside the leg side and slaps the length delivery over extra cover for a one-bounce four, take a bow AB.. what a dynamite of a player, that shot gives SA the series win

commentPostTextItems.html: So that is all from us from this series. Firdose will be analysing the series and please keep an eye for that. Thanks for all your comments and feedback, for now this is Devashish Fuloria signing off, ciao ciao.

AB de Villliers: "It was a great team effort. It was a pleasure playing here in Benoni, and it was a great series and well-played by Pakistan team too. It is always easy turning back to Dale, but the whole bowling unit got better and better. Ryan is one of those guys, he just makes it happen, he got Misbah and Afridi in one over and that was a big game changer. Pakistan are a world-class team, they will surely climb the world-rankings soon and good luck to them. I am in good form at the moment, but I am not probably timing it as well as I like to."
AB wins both Man of the Match and the Man of the Series awards

Misbah: "I think it was a 250 pitch and it was gettable the way we started, but we lost wickets at crucial times and chose wrong shots, but SA played really well. We had a good partnership in the middle and we should have stretched it was 1 10 more overs. (on AB's drop) These things happen in cricket. But Irfan bowled really well throughout the series and gave us all the crucial breakthroughs, he just needs to work on his fitness a bit. The team got some confidence during the series, we just need to play quality cricket and keep competing. We could have really enjoyed had we won this one, but still a good series. "

The match had all the makings of a good contest here in Benoni, but Pakistan fell short by 30-40 runs on a pitch that had enough on it to keep the bowlers in business. But it came down to the experience and the brilliance of AB de Villiers to steer the chase and do this easily for South Africa. Farhan Behaardien played a mature innings too and well supported his captain. So SA remains one destination where Pakistan haven't won an ODI series. Stick around because we will have the pearls from captains in just a bit...
luke: "may SA's river of off-nights continue long into the future!! yet another good win:)"
suhail shafi shah: "well played S.A. and Pakistan.. both of u entertained us for last 3 months or so.. congrates S.A. & A.B. for outperforming Pak when it mattered..."
Osama Baig: "... Aaaaannnd the trend continues. Screen matches in university = Pakistan loses. (No, AB had nothing to do with it)"

commentPreTextItems.html: Magpie: "Even chokers can have an off night. After all, that's how they win..."

commentTextItems.html: makes room by arching his back and steers it to deep backward point for a couple, he is into the nineties
a rare play and a miss by AB as he tries to push the length delivery through cover
he bends down on his knee and slaps it over mid-off for a flat....six, is it? well almost, just bounces inside the boundary
length ball outside off, the batsman pushes it firmly through cover where the fielder dives over the ball and allows it to go through, not very good by Farhat there..

commentPreTextItems.html: Wahab comes from over the wicket

commentTextItems.html: he walks across the stumps and punches it to deep midwicket for a single
slower this time and tossed up, he defends it towards midwicket

commentPostTextItems.html: SafferBoy: "Funny how SA are chokers when Sri Lanka has lost -if I'm not mistaken- 4 consecutive finals that they've played in...Surely they hold the title now?"

commentTextItems.html: oh lovely hit through cover! It was quicker on the off stump, he waited for it on the back foot and spanks it through covers off the back foot, the fielders had no chance to move
quicker delivery, it's full too, flicked down to fine-leg for a single
goes for a sweep, but misses as he is hit on the pads, but it was sliding down the leg side
pushed through on the stumps, the batsman punches it to mid-on

commentPreTextItems.html: Ryan: "Funny how people think SA have no chance of winning Champions Trophy based on past history - yet SA won it in 1998. It's a forgettable tournament tbh."

commentTextItems.html: comes down the track, gets under the ball and sends it over the deep midwicket boundary, easily done
pushed through on the stumps, AB defends it solidly to midwicket

headshotImage.caption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentPreTextItems.html: Ravindra Jadeja: "Trott, you were saying something ???"

commentTextItems.html: he goes on the back foot and punches the quicker delivery to short cover
another one on the pads, it's flicked to short fine-leg this time
fuller length on the pads, hit straight to the same fielder
flatter delivery on the pads, the batsman works it straight to backward square leg
he skips down the track but doesn't get any bat on it, the ball hits the pads and goes to short fine leg
he goes back to the quicker delivery and defends it towards midwicket

commentPostTextItems.html: gav: "South Africa are a good solid well structured side surely. But they are the best chokers at international tournaments."

dismissalComment.html: the batsman dabs the flatter delivery to square leg, but Wahab runs halfway down the pitch. Robbie P actually breaks the stumps with his leg, but he realises that in time, so uproots the stump to complete the run out. Wahab was still nowhere near.
